Mode-aware vim border + cursor + truecolor palette resolution.

Border / cursor:
  vim NORMAL  → input border in default color, cursor block
  vim INSERT  → input border in color_input_border_insert, cursor bar

Truecolor:
  parse_color preserves hex strings as RGB tuples instead of snapping to
  the xterm-256 cube via closest_color. tui.init_pair allocates curses
  palette slots (init_color, slots 232+ which endcord's bundled palette
  doesn't reference) so themes render their actual hex values when the
  terminal supports ccc (kitty does). Falls back to closest_color if
  can_change_color() is false or the slot range is exhausted.

Adds one new theme key, color_input_border_insert (default [-1, -1] so
non-customizing users keep current behavior).

